{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883999081,"sessionID":"ses_28510e762ffeZGYsWDSVWsV5pr","part":{"id":"prt_d7aef572a001bMhlA56i24dPt7","messageID":"msg_d7aef3997001kNNNpjwBaYgZUU","sessionID":"ses_28510e762ffeZGYsWDSVWsV5pr","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-cd8c212bcc844f3eb263a727e75afab3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-029/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-029/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-029 — SDK HTTP 底层客户端 Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-029 — SDK HTTP 底层客户端 |\n8: | Module | `sdk-python` |\n9: | Language | Python |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Task Checklist\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: HTTP Session Configuration (ST-1)\n18: \n19: - [ ] **T1.1**: Implement `DEFAULT_TIMEOUT = 120` constant in `http.py`\n20:   - Purpose: Define default read timeout constant\n21:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py`\n22:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.utils.http import DEFAULT_TIMEOUT; print(DEFAULT_TIMEOUT)\"`\n23: \n24: - [ ] **T1.2**: Implement `DEFAULT_CONNECT_TIMEOUT = 5.0` constant in `http.py`\n25:   - Purpose: Define default connection timeout constant\n26:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py`\n27:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.utils.http import DEFAULT_CONNECT_TIMEOUT; print(DEFAULT_CONNECT_TIMEOUT)\"`\n28: \n29: - [ ] **T1.3**: Implement `DEFAULT_POOL_CONNECTIONS = 10` constant in `http.py`\n30:   - Purpose: Define default connection pool size constant\n31:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py`\n32:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.utils.http import DEFAULT_POOL_CONNECTIONS; print(DEFAULT_POOL_CONNECTIONS)\"`\n33: \n34: - [ ] **T1.4**: Implement `DEFAULT_POOL_MAXSIZE = 10` constant in `http.py`\n35:   - Purpose: Define default maximum pool connections constant\n36:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py`\n37:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.utils.http import DEFAULT_POOL_MAXSIZE; print(DEFAULT_POOL_MAXSIZE)\"`\n38: \n39: - [ ] **T1.5**: Enhance `create_session` to accept `timeout` and `connect_timeout` kwargs\n40:   - Purpose: Allow custom timeout configuration on session creation\n41:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py`\n42:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_http_utils.py::TestCreateSessionTimeout -v`\n43: \n44: - [ ] **T1.6**: Implement `create_session` with default headers parameter\n45:   - Purpose: Allow setting default headers on session creation\n46:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py`\n47:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_http_utils.py::TestCreateSessionHeaders -v`\n48: \n49: - [ ] **T1.7**: Implement `create_session` with retry configuration parameter\n50:   - Purpose: Allow configuring retry behavior for transient failures\n51:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py`\n52:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_http_utils.py::TestCreateSessionRetry -v`\n53: \n54: ### Phase 2: Retry Handler Implementation (ST-2)\n55: \n56: - [ ] **T2.1**: Implement `RetryConfig` dataclass with `max_retries`, `backoff_factor`, `retry_on` parameters\n57:   - Purpose: Define retry configuration structure\n58:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py`\n59:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_http_utils.py::TestRetryConfig -v`\n60: \n61: - [ ] **T2.2**: Implement `DEFAULT_RETRY_CONFIG` with `max_retries=3`, `backoff_factor=0.5`\n62:   - Purpose: Define default retry configuration for transient errors\n63:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py`\n64:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.utils.http import DEFAULT_RETRY_CONFIG; print(DEFAULT_RETRY_CONFIG)\"`\n65: \n66: - [ ] **T2.3**: Implement `RetryHTTPAdapter` extending `HTTPAdapter`\n67:   - Purpose: Custom HTTPAdapter with retry logic\n68:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py`\n69:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_http_utils.py::TestRetryHTTPAdapter -v`\n70: \n71: - [ ] **T2.4**: Implement `RetryHTTPAdapter` retry on 5xx status codes\n72:   - Purpose: Retry on server errors (500, 502, 503, 504)\n73:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py`\n74:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_http_utils.py::TestRetryOn5xx -v`\n75: \n76: - [ ] **T2.5**: Implement `RetryHTTPAdapter` retry on connection errors\n77:   - Purpose: Retry on `ConnectionError`, `Timeout` exceptions\n78:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py`\n79:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_http_utils.py::TestRetryOnConnectionError -v`\n80: \n81: - [ ] **T2.6**: Implement `RetryHTTPAdapter` exponential backoff\n82:   - Purpose: Implement backoff_factor * (2 ** (retry_count - 1)) delay\n83:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py`\n84:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_http_utils.py::TestExponentialBackoff -v`\n85: \n86: ### Phase 3: HTTP Request Helper Functions (ST-3)\n87: \n88: - [ ] **T3.1**: Implement `make_timeout_tuple(connect_timeout, read_timeout)` helper\n89:   - Purpose: Create requests timeout tuple (connect_timeout, read_timeout)\n90:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py`\n91:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_http_utils.py::TestMakeTimeoutTuple -v`\n92: \n93: - [ ] **T3.2**: Implement `make_timeout_tuple` with default values fallback\n94:   - Purpose: Use DEFAULT_CONNECT_TIMEOUT and DEFAULT_TIMEOUT when not specified\n95:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py`\n96:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_http_utils.py::TestMakeTimeoutTupleDefaults -v`\n97: \n98: - [ ] **T3.3**: Implement `is_retryable_error(exception)` helper function\n99:   - Purpose: Determine if an exception is retryable\n100:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py`\n101:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_http_utils.py::TestIsRetryableError -v`\n102: \n103: - [ ] **T3.4**: Implement `is_retryable_status(status_code)` helper function\n104:   - Purpose: Determine if HTTP status code is retryable (5xx)\n105:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py`\n106:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_http_utils.py::TestIsRetryableStatus -v`\n107: \n108: ### Phase 4: Session Header Constants (ST-4)\n109: \n110: - [ ] **T4.1**: Implement `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"` constant\n111:   - Purpose: Define session header name used by data plane clients\n112:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py`\n113:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.utils.http import SESSION_HEADER; print(SESSION_HEADER)\"`\n114: \n115: - [ ] **T4.2**: Implement `CONTENT_TYPE_JSON = \"application/json\"` constant\n116:   - Purpose: Define JSON content type header value\n117:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py`\n118:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.utils.http import CONTENT_TYPE_JSON; print(CONTENT_TYPE_JSON)\"`\n119: \n120: - [ ] **T4.3**: Implement `AUTH_HEADER = \"Authorization\"` constant\n121:   - Purpose: Define authorization header name\n122:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py`\n123:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.utils.http import AUTH_HEADER; print(AUTH_HEADER)\"`\n124: \n125: ### Phase 5: Update Client Constants (ST-5)\n126: \n127: - [ ] **T5.1**: Update `ControlPlaneClient` to use `http.py` constants\n128:   - Purpose: Replace local constants with imported defaults\n129:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n130:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_control_plane.py -v`\n131: \n132: - [ ] **T5.2**: Update `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` to use `http.py` constants\n133:   - Purpose: Replace local constants with imported defaults\n134:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n135:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_data_plane.py -v`\n136: \n137: - [ ] **T5.3**: Update `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` to use `http.py` constants\n138:   - Purpose: Replace local constants with imported defaults\n139:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n140:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py -v`\n141: \n142: ### Phase 6: Unit Tests for HTTP Utilities (ST-6)\n143: \n144: - [ ] **T6.1**: Create `tests/test_http_utils.py` test file\n145:   - Purpose: Test file for HTTP utilities module\n146:   - File: `sdk-python/tests/test_http_utils.py`\n147:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_http_utils.py -v`\n148: \n149: - [ ] **T6.2**: Test `DEFAULT_TIMEOUT` constant value\n150:   - Purpose: Verify DEFAULT_TIMEOUT = 120\n151:   - File: `sdk-python/tests/test_http_utils.py`\n152:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_http_utils.py::TestConstants::test_default_timeout -v`\n153: \n154: - [ ] **T6.3**: Test `DEFAULT_CONNECT_TIMEOUT` constant value\n155:   - Purpose: Verify DEFAULT_CONNECT_TIMEOUT = 5.0\n156:   - File: `sdk-python/tests/test_http_utils.py`\n157:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_http_utils.py::TestConstants::test_default_connect_timeout -v`\n158: \n159: - [ ] **T6.4**: Test `create_session` returns requests.Session\n160:   - Purpose: Verify session type and adapters\n161:   - File: `sdk-python/tests/test_http_utils.py`\n162:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_http_utils.py::TestCreateSession::test_returns_session -v`\n163: \n164: - [ ] **T6.5**: Test `create_session` custom pool settings\n165:   - Purpose: Verify pool_connections and pool_maxsize configurable\n166:   - File: `sdk-python/tests/test_http_utils.py`\n167:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_http_utils.py::TestCreateSession::test_custom_pool -v`\n168: \n169: - [ ] **T6.6**: Test `create_session` with default headers\n170:   - Purpose: Ver